## {{!linkable_header('Green lights for equation evaluation')}}


Try your luck at the Pythagorean Theorem.
Remember, the evaluation of each answer will be done by a computer program.
Therefore the _normal_ computer operators will be used.
<div class="row">
 <div class="twocolumns">
<table>
 <thead>
  <tr>
  <th>Operation</th> <th>Operator<br/>Symbol</th>
 </thead
 <tbody>
  <tr> <td>Addition      </td> <td>+</td> </tr>
  <tr> <td>Multiplication</td> <td>*</td> </tr>
  <tr> <td>Division      </td> <td>/</td> </tr>
  <tr> <td>Exponent, for a^2 or $a^2$  </td> <td>&#x2a;&#x2a;</td> </tr>
  <tr> <td>Square root, for a^0.5 or $\sqrt{a}$  </td> <td>&#x2a;&#x2a;0.5 or sqrt()</td> </tr>
 </tbody>
</table>
 </div>
</div>


Variable names are **case sensitive**.
Therefore, use lower-case $a$, $b$, and $c$, for the following equations.
Using an upper-case version of the variables will result in an <font color="red">unknown: No globals A</font> message.

<div class="row">
 <div class="threefourthcolumns">
Pythagorean.Theorem.1: Given a right triangle with sides 
$a$ of length 3 and $b$ of length 4, what is the length of 
hypotenuse $c$?  
% answer = 'sqrt(a*a + b*b)'
{{!expression(answer, dict(a=3, b=4), points=5, name='Pythagorean.Theorem.1')}}<br/>
% include('viewAnswer')

<p/>
Note that an acceptable answer can use 
numerical equations like $3**2$,
symbolical values in equations like $a+b$,
both numbers and symbols like $a**2$,
integer values like 37,
or float values like 37.0. <br/>

<p/>
Each correct solution will be highlighted in <font color='green'>green</font> whenever 
the answer is finished.
The system assumes input is finished when you click outside the input box.
 </div>
 <div class="fourcolumns">
  <img src="{{static('images/triangle.png')}}" style="width:80%; float:right" />
 </div>
</div>

Try another question. 
But for this one, you cannot enter numeric values.
You may only use symbols $a$ and $b$ and apply mathematical computation on them.  

Remember: The multiplication symbol is the asterisk, `*`.
Addition is the plus sign, `+`.
Exponential notation uses two asterisks, `**`.
Square root is a number raised to the 0.5 power.

**Pythagorean.Theorem.2:** Given a right triangle of sides $a$ and $b$, 
what is the length of the hypotenuse?
% answer = '(a ** 2 + b ** 2) ** 0.5'
{{!expression(answer, dict(a=5, b=12), dict(a=3, b=4), points=5, name='Pythagorean.Theorem.2')}}
% include('viewAnswer')

Let's try one more to see if you can apply what you learned.

**Pythagorean.Theorem.3:** Given a right triangle of sides $a$ and hypotenuse $c$,
what is the length of side $b$?  
% answer = 'sqrt(c**2 - a*a)'
{{!expression(answer, dict(a=5, c=13), dict(a=3, c=5), dict(a=4, c=5), points=10, name='Pythagorean.Theorem.3')}}
% include('viewAnswer')


