## {{!linkable_header('No partial credit in COMP 421')}}

Per the [syllabus]({{get_url('syllabi', page_name='syllabus')}}) there is no partial credit in COMP 421.
There is <font color='green'>green</font> highlights as described in the [grading feedback]({{get_url('syllabi', page_name='syllabus')}}#grading-feedback).

For [games]({{get_url('syllabi', page_name='syllabus')}}#games) and
[worksheets]({{get_url('syllabi', page_name='syllabus')}}#worksheets)
the minimum grade for an on-time submission is 50%.
For any game segment or worksheet correctly answering 75% or better will receive a score of a 100%.

For [homeworks]({{get_url('syllabi', page_name='syllabus')}}#homework-assignments) and
[exams]({{get_url('syllabi', page_name='syllabus')}}#exams), the syllabus describes how
[subsequent submissions]({{get_url('syllabi', page_name='syllabus')}}#subsequent-submissions)
increases the score of the assessment.

This is a form of partial credit that depends on waiting for the grader to complete,
correcting incorrect answers, and resubmission.
The [syllabus subsequent submissions]({{get_url('syllabi', page_name='syllabus')}}#subseqent-submission) describes
how the grading works.

**Subsequent.Submissions:** Assuming for a homework an initial submission was 75%,
the second submission was 90%,
the third submissions was 100%, 
and a fourth submission was 100%, 
what would be the final overall score for the homework?   
% answer = '75 +(90 -75)/2 + (100-90)/3 + 0/4'
% answer2 = f'''
The first submission counts for 75%
The second submission adds (90 - 75)/2 or {(90-75)/2}%
The third submission add (100 - max(90, 75))/3 or {(100 - max(90, 75))/3}%
The fourth submission adds (100 - max(90, 75, 100))/4 or 0%

Answer: {answer} or {round(eval(answer), 2)}'''
{{!expression(answer, dict(P=[75, 90, 100, 100]), points=15, name='Subsequent.Submissions')}}
% include('viewAnswer', answer=answer2)

